column5: 'Does the patient have fever? Measured through thermometer or feeling the body'
'Did the patient seek care? Within 24 hours of onset of fever or other symptoms?'
'Severe symptoms? Is patient unconscious or having bleeding, jaundice or severe pallor?'
'Vomiting Measured through thermometer or feeling the body'
'Taking medication with food Within 24 hours of onset of fever or other symptoms'
'Side effects If you have dark coloured urine, stop taking your Primaquine and go to the nearest healt center'
'When to get help If you do not feel better within 3 days or start to feel much worse, go to the nearest health facility for further care'
'Travelling Has the patient travelled overnight away from home within the previous two weeks'
'LLIN Did the patient sleep under a LLIN last night'
'LLIN Does the patient\'s household own a LLIN?'
